# Backend Migration & Segmentation Refactor Plan

## Goal
Shift the image processing pipeline from the frontend (Android Native Module) to the backend (Python/OpenCV). The goal is to perform true flood-fill region extraction with vector contour generation (`findContours` + `approxPolyDP`) on the backend, converting the React Native frontend into a pure high-performance rendering engine using Skia and Reanimated.

## 🔴 Deletions & Code Removal
The current client-side processing architecture is being completely scrapped in favor of server-side processing.

### 1. [src/screens/GameScreen.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sumit/colorArt/src/screens/GameScreen.tsx)
**Regions to Delete:**
*   **Lines 8-36:** `edgeDetectionShader` (Edge detection moves to backend).
*   **Lines 53-71:** [createBlobPath](file:///c:/Users/sumit/colorArt/src/screens/GameScreen.tsx#53-72) helper.
*   **Lines 88-125:** `rasterData` `useMemo` block (Grid-based mapping removed completely).
*   **Lines 131-146:** [handleRasterTap](file:///c:/Users/sumit/colorArt/src/screens/GameScreen.tsx#131-147) function.
*   **Lines 261-318, 341-367:** `loadedImage`, `RnImage`, `SkiaImage` shader rendering and number hints overlay (Frontend will no longer render bitmap overlays or raster modes, only vector paths).

